---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About KAI OS | Modular AI Operating System"
  description="Learn about KAI OS, a modular AI operating system for automation, research, content creation, digital business, and long-term intelligent workflows."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="page-main">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="page-kicker">About KAI OS</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">A modular AI operating system built for practical long-term workflows.</h1>
        <p class="page-lede">
          KAI OS is designed as a growing ecosystem of agents, documentation, workflows, and review systems that help creators and builders move from ideas to organized execution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-section">
      <div class="container content-grid">
        <article class="content-card wide-card">
          <h2>Mission</h2>
          <p>
            The mission of KAI OS is to make AI useful as an operating layer for research, creation, automation, digital business, and continuous improvement while keeping human oversight clear.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-card">
          <h2>Principles</h2>
          <p>
            Modular design, controlled execution, documentation-first decisions, practical output, and safety boundaries guide the platform.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-card">
          <h2>Positioning</h2>
          <p>
            KAI OS is not a generic chatbot. It is a structured AI operating system for agents, workflows, reports, launch planning, and future intelligent systems.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-card wide-card">
          <h2>Current Focus</h2>
          <p>
            The current focus is launch readiness: turning validated AI-assisted content and operational planning into a simple, reviewable public presence.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
